<span id="freeTextContainer10449337780357640829">In this story LeCarre takes us on a trip into the schizophrenic world of creating legends and running spies. <br/><br/>It was set during the early 1980&apos;s when terrorist bombings had become common place in Europe. And there were characters in this story that reminded me of the BaderMinehoff(sp?) Group. <br/><br/>Even though some of the elements in this story are dated, it is still a powerful novel.<br/><br/>And after a spate of reading not so great Le Carre novels, this one was very refreshing.</span>
